narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I really enjoyed how this course was set up. On Tuesday we would be given a lecture by Professor Musser about the week's films and other background information that was relevant to that week's theme. Then Wednesday was the film screening. And then Thursday was set up like a discussion section where everyone in the class would talk about their responses to the films.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, reasonable workload, instructor is very knowledgeable. Don't be scared to take it without prior exposure to the topic.
I loved this class. It was a decent time commitment, as any film class, but very informative and engaging.
